COUNT.
MUST: emit EXACTLY one clause for every numbered segment, reusing its "n".
MUST NOT: merge two segments, add any, or skip the last one.
OK: 4 segments → 4 clauses with n=1..4.
ERROR: 4 segments → 3 clauses (you merged «save» and «share»).

ANAPHORA — pronouns and implied objects, to be resolved BEFORE choosing the object.
MUST: if a segment uses an enclitic pronoun (-lo/-la/-li/-le/-ne/-melo…) or an
  implied object (e.g. «find where they were taken»), replace the pronoun
  with the NOUN it refers to, taken from a PRECEDING segment, and write it in "ref".
MUST NOT: choose verb/object from the naked pronoun or the verb alone; MUST NOT inherit
  the previous object by inertia — the antecedent is the NOUN, not the previously chosen object.
  A recipient «to/with <Name>» or «with contact X» is the RECIPIENT, not the patient.
MUST: deduce verb and object ONLY from "ref" (the clause with the replaced antecedent).
OK: «…save photos to /tmp, and share them with Lucia» → ref of 2nd = «share THE PHOTOS with Lucia» → {share, files}.
ERROR: «share them» read as {share, contacts} because «-le»/«Lucia» lost the antecedent «photos».

BOUNDARIES/OBJECT.
MUST: for each "ref" choose the verb whose BOUNDARY (above) matches and the object from the
  NOUN of the clause. MUST NOT copy a verb due to word similarity with an example.

